A vintage 1980s computer workspace scene with a warm sepia-toned palette, featuring an old CRT monitor displaying a text editor with curly bracket symbols scattered across the screen like friendly punctuation marks. On the wooden desk beside the computer sits a small ceramic cup holding a handlebar mustache shape made of twisted wire, playfully referencing the template syntax. Scattered paper documents with merge fields indicated by curly bracket cutouts create a collage effect, with some papers appearing to float and transform into digital pixels as they approach the screen. The scene is lit by a warm desk lamp casting nostalgic amber shadows, evoking the evolution from physical mail merge to digital templating. Dust motes float in the lamplight, adding to the nostalgic atmosphere of early computing meeting modern web development.
